# Solo OS — Flutter Architecture Rules

## Core Principle
**UI observes. ViewModels think. Services act. Repositories store.**
No business logic in widgets. No storage calls in screens.

---

## 1. File Size Limits

- Screens: max 200 lines
- ViewModels: max 150 lines
- Widgets: max 100 lines
- Services/Repositories: max 150 lines

If a file exceeds these limits → extract widgets, split logic, or introduce a ViewModel.

---

## 2. Feature Structure

Every new feature MUST follow this layout:

```
lib/features/<feature_name>/
  presentation/
    screens/         ← StatelessWidget or minimal StatefulWidget
    widgets/         ← extracted private widgets
    viewmodels/      ← ChangeNotifier, business logic, state
  data/
    repositories/    ← abstracts storage + remote calls
  domain/
    models/          ← pure data classes (if feature-specific)
```

Shared/reused code goes in:
```
lib/core/
  utils/             ← calculators, formatters, helpers
  theme/             ← AppColors, AppTheme (already exists)

lib/shared/
  widgets/           ← reusable UI components (AppBottomSheet, DismissibleCard, etc.)
  services/          ← cross-feature services (ClaudeService, StorageService)
  models/            ← cross-feature models (app_models.dart)
  l10n/              ← localization
```

---

## 3. Screen Rules

Screens are THIN. They:
- Build layout from ViewModel state
- Call ViewModel methods on user interaction
- Do NOT call StorageService or ClaudeService directly
- Do NOT contain `if/else` business logic
- Do NOT compute derived values (sums, filters, counts)

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
class IdeasScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {
    final vm = context.watch<IdeasViewModel>();
    return Scaffold(
      body: vm.isLoading ? const LoadingWidget() : IdeasList(ideas: vm.activeIdeas),
      floatingActionButton: FloatingActionButton(onPressed: vm.showAddDialog),
    );
  }
}

// ❌ WRONG — business logic in screen
class IdeasScreen extends StatefulWidget {
  void _addIdea() async {
    final ideas = _storage.getIdeas();
    if (ideas.length >= 3) { ... } // ← this belongs in ViewModel
  }
}
```

---

## 4. ViewModel Rules

ViewModels are ChangeNotifiers that:
- Hold all state for one screen
- Call repositories for data
- Call services (Claude, Calendar) for external operations
- Expose clean `bool isLoading`, `String? error`, typed data getters
- NEVER import Flutter widgets (no `package:flutter/widgets.dart` imports of UI)

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
class IdeasViewModel extends ChangeNotifier {
  final StorageService _storage;
  List<Idea> _ideas = [];
  bool _isValidating = false;

  List<Idea> get activeIdeas => _ideas.where((i) => i.status == IdeaStatus.active).toList();
  bool get isValidating => _isValidating;

  Future<void> validateIdea(Idea idea) async {
    _isValidating = true;
    notifyListeners();
    // ... call ClaudeService, update idea, save
    _isValidating = false;
    notifyListeners();
  }
}
```

---

## 5. Widget Extraction Rules

Extract a widget when:
- A widget tree is >30 lines
- It appears more than once
- It has its own meaningful name (e.g., IdeaCard, HabitRow, BirthdayTile)

Private widgets (`_MyWidget`) are fine WITHIN the same file if small.
Once a file exceeds 200 lines → the private widgets must move to `widgets/`.

---

## 6. Modal Bottom Sheet

Always use the shared `AppBottomSheet.show()` helper:

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
AppBottomSheet.show(context, builder: (ctx) => AddIdeaForm(...));

// ❌ WRONG — inline boilerplate
showModalBottomSheet(
  backgroundColor: AppColors.card,
  shape: const RoundedRectangleBorder(borderRadius: BorderRadius.vertical(top: Radius.circular(20))),
  ...
)
```

---

## 7. Dismissible List Items

Always use `DismissibleCard` widget:

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT
DismissibleCard(id: item.id, onDelete: () => vm.delete(item), child: MyTile(...));

// ❌ WRONG — inline Dismissible boilerplate
Dismissible(key: Key(item.id), background: Container(alignment: Alignment.centerRight, ...), ...)
```

---

## 8. Storage Access

Screens and widgets NEVER call StorageService directly.
Only ViewModels and Repositories access StorageService.

---

## 9. Localization

All user-visible strings use `ls.t('key')`.
No hardcoded English strings in widgets or screens.
New keys must be added to ALL three languages (en, ru, ky) in app_strings.dart.

---

## 10. Naming Conventions

| Type | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Screen | `<Feature>Screen` | `IdeasScreen` |
| ViewModel | `<Feature>ViewModel` | `IdeasViewModel` |
| Repository | `<Feature>Repository` | `IdeasRepository` |
| Widget (private) | `_<Name>` | `_IdeaCard` |
| Widget (shared) | `<Name>Widget` or `<Name>` | `DismissibleCard` |
| Feature folder | snake_case | `features/ideas/` |

---

## 11. Migration Strategy

This codebase is being migrated incrementally. Legacy files in `lib/screens/` are valid.
New features → MUST use feature-based structure.
Refactoring old features → MUST follow this guide.
Do NOT break working screens while refactoring.

---

## 12. State Management

We use **Provider + ChangeNotifier** (already in pubspec).
- One ViewModel per screen/feature
- Register in `main.dart` or the relevant widget tree via `ChangeNotifierProvider`
- Consume with `context.watch<VM>()` or `context.read<VM>()`

Do NOT introduce new state management libraries (Riverpod, Bloc) without team agreement.
